Fifty-seven MCAs from Nairobi county have signed a petition to impeach Speaker Alex ole Magelo. Makongeni ward rep Peter Imwatok, who sponsored the censure motion, said the Speaker has eroded the dignity, character and esteem of MCAs."We are concerned that the speaker has failed in his duty as enshrined in the constitution to protect the dignity, honour and respect of this assembly," the motion reads in part.Imwatok said on Thursday that the Assembly has expressed displeasure and disappointment with Magelo and want to remove him.At least one third of the 127 members need to sign the petition for it to be approved for debate by the Speaker.